"'''Taster's Choice: The Tale of Jabba's Chef'''" is a short story by [[Barbara Hambly]] that tells the story of [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt's]] [[Chef/Legends|chef]], [[Porcellus/Legends|Porcellus]] which was published in ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'' [[December]] [[1995]] by [[Bantam Spectra]].

==Plot summary==
The ever-fretful [[Porcellus/Legends|Porcellus]] is the head [[Chef/Legends|chef]] in [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]]. He avoids displeasing the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] with [[Foodstuff/Legends|food]] and attempts to maintain a low profile and humble kitchen. Until he  hears that [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] suspects him of putting ''fierfek'' in his food – a [[Huttese/Legends|Huttese]] term that Porcellus takes to mean [[Poison/Legends|"poison"]]. He knows that one bad meal would be a [[Death/Legends|death]] sentence. When the dead body of [[Weequay/Legends|Weequay]] [[Sail barge/Legends|sail barge]] [[Captain/Legends|captain]], [[Ak-Buz]], turns up near the kitchen, a terrified Porcellus hides the corpse lest he be a suspect. In the midst of [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] rescue of his friends from Jabba's clutches, Porcellus learns the true definition of ''fierfek'' from [[C-3PO/Legends|Skywalker's droid]]. It translates not to "poison" but to "hex," and sure enough misfortune has followed many who have tasted Porcellus' wares.

